.TH "TextDecoderStream.TextDecoderStream" "JS" "December 8, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
TextDecoderStream.TextDecoderStream \- TextDecoderStream:
TextDecoderStream() constructor
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]TextDecoderStream()\f[B]\f[R] constructor creates a new
\f[CR]TextDecoderStream\f[R] object which is used to convert a stream of
text in a binary encoding into strings.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
new TextDecoderStream(label)
new TextDecoderStream(label, options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]label\f[R]
A string defaulting to \f[CR]utf\-8\f[R].
This may be any valid label.
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An object with the following properties:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]fatal\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A boolean value indicating if the \f[CR]TextDecoder.decode()\f[R] method
must throw a \f[CR]TypeError\f[R] when decoding invalid data.
It defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R], which means that the decoder will
substitute malformed data with a replacement character.
.TP
\f[B]ignoreBOM\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A boolean value indicating whether the \c
.UR https://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-byte-order-mark
byte order mark
.UE \c
\ will be included in the output or skipped over.
It defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R], which means that the byte order mark
will be skipped over when decoding and will not be included in the
decoded text.
.RE
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown if the value of \f[CR]label\f[R] is unknown, or is one of the
values leading to a \f[CR]\[aq]replacement\[aq]\f[R] decoding algorithm
(\f[CR]\[dq]iso\-2022\-cn\[dq]\f[R] or
\f[CR]\[dq]iso\-2022\-cn\-ext\[dq]\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
The following example demonstrates how to decode binary data retrieved
from a \f[CR]fetch()\f[R] call.
The data will be interpreted as UTF\-8, as no \f[CR]label\f[R] has been
passed.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] response = \f[B]await\f[R] fetch(\[dq]https://example.com\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] stream = response.body.pipeThrough(\f[B]new\f[R] TextDecoderStream());
.EE
